# Architecture map (Trello Cerveau)

Static HTML/JS/CSS Power-Up — **no bundler**. Scripts load via `<script>` and attach to `window.*`. Prefer reading the file header TOC before diving into a mega-file.

## Entry pages

| Page | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.html` | Power-Up connector + capability registration |
| `popup.html` | Card editor (priority / progrès / agent / info) |
| `settings.html` | Board settings (statut, formula, goals, …) |
| `profile.html` | Member preferences (`UserProfile`) |
| `gantt.html` | Full-screen Gantt |
| `assistant.html` | Project-scope assistant window |
| `memory-*.html` | Memory alignment surfaces |

## Layering (keep boundaries)

```
UI (*-ui.js)  →  pure helpers (PriorityUI, GanttModel, AgentBlocks)
              →  Trello bridges (*-trello.js)  →  pluginData / REST
AgentUI       →  PriorityAgent (LLM)          →  executeActions(bridge)
```

- **UI modules** must not call Trello REST directly; take a bridge/`t` from the page.
- **`PriorityUI` / `GanttModel` / `AgentBlocks`** are pure (or DOM-only) — no pluginData.
- **`*-trello.js`** own persistence keys and badge/capability handlers.
- **`PriorityAgent`** owns prompts, chat protocol, and action execution; **`AgentUI`** is chrome only.

## Largest modules (start here)

| File (~lines) | Global | One-line role |
|---------------|--------|---------------|
| `components/priority/priority-ui.js` (~21k) | `PriorityUI` | Scoring, markdown, due/statut/overview field factories, color schemes |
